Rustenburg &#x2013; Two boys died and another is recuperating in hospital after they ate potato chips in Makgobistad, the North West provincial government said on Wednesday.&#x201C;We send our heartfelt condolences to the family affected by this tragedy. We will do whatever we can do from our side to provide support to the family during this difficult time,&#x201D; said premier Supra Mahumapelo.The two boys aged 10 and 12 years died at a local clinic on Tuesday evening. They fell sick after eating some potato chips and drinking tap water from a 25 litre container at home in the late afternoon.The third child, a 15-year-old was recuperating at Bophelong Hospital in Mahikeng. A medical report on the incident has not yet been released.The provincial department of social development would, in the meantime, visit the family to assist with counselling and determine what form of support will be required by the family.A memorial service was planned for Thursday, at Makgobistad Community Hall. African News Agency IOL News on Facebook IOL on Twitter